<<<<<<< HEAD
 This check monitors the temperature sensors of ACME devices which support ACMEPACKET-ENVMON-MIB.
 The state is OK if "initial" or "normal" is reported, it is WARN if "minor" or
 "major" and CRIT if "critical", "shutdown", "not present", "not functioning" or
 "unknown".

 Upper and lower levels can be set. There are no default levels.

item:
 The name of the temperature sensor.

inventory:
 One service per sensor is created.
=======
 This check monitors the temperature sensors of ACME devices.

 The state is

 - {OK} if "initial" or "normal"

 - {WARN} if "minor" or "major"

 - {CRIT} if "critical", "shutdown", "not present", "not functioning" or "unknown"

 is reported.

 Upper and lower levels have to be configured.
 There are no default levels.

 This check uses the ACMEPACKET-ENVMON-MIB.

item:
 Name of the temperature sensor.

inventory:
 One service is created for each temperature sensor.
